=Description=

"Open Media advocates hold the concept that the content they create is fairly and freely distributed, while credit is still given to the creator. The creator can retain rights but still allow the content to move beyond boundaries and restrictions of the middle man. It is a relationship between the creator and the consumer.

Open Media can encompass everything from books to stories to video to music to art to even virtual worlds and games."
(http://openmediareview.com/about-2/)


